sec.p:
As the first step of our pipeline for identifying antimicrobial peptides, the classification task aims to perform coarse-grained filtering, significantly reducing the number of sequences in our vast candidate library to manageable levels. For the classification model, we fine-tune the protein pre-training model ESM-1b11 with a frozen bottom layer up to layer 32, while only adjusting the parameters of the last Bert layer (layer 33). Specifically, the final representation of a sequence is obtained from the [CLS] token of ESM-1b’s last layer, which is then fed into a classification head composed of multiple MLP layers. Adam optimizer is chosen with a learning rate of 1e-4, more details can be found in our code. For this binary classification task, we employ the binary-cross-entropy loss function\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
