For example, during a specific iteration, K sequences were randomly sampled from the dataset. Subsequently, these sequences were ranked based on their Minimum Inhibitory Concentration (MIC) values, with lower MIC values corresponding to higher rankings. In cases where negative samples shared identical MIC values, they were assigned the same rank. This procedure allowed the derivation of relative scores \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
