For the cytotoxicity test, 1×104 NIH 3T3 cells were seeded into each well of the 96-well plates and cultured at 37 °C overnight. Then the culture medium was removed and the peptides at the desired concentrations in the media were added to each well (n = 5). The cells were cultured for another 24 h, followed by replacing the media with 10% CCK-8 containing fresh DMEM and another 2 h incubation. The absorbance of the solution was measured at 450 nm by a microplate reader. Cell viability was calculated using the following equation.6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
